Let $E \rightarrow \mathbb{R}^3$ be a 3-dimensional vector bundle with fiber $\mathbb{R}^2$, such that the transition functions $g_{ij}: U_i \cap U_j \rightarrow GL_2(\mathbb{R})$ are given by 
$$
g_{ij}(x,y,z) = 
\begin{pmatrix}
    x^2 + 2xy & -y^2 \\
    0 & \frac{1}{x+y+1}
\end{pmatrix}
$$
where $U_1 = \{(x,y,z) \in \mathbb{R}^3 | x > 0\}, U_2 = \{(x,y,z) \in \mathbb{R}^3 | y > 0\}$.
Find the Euler class $e(E)$ of the vector bundle $E$.
